        "description": "QR Code Link to This Post Welcome to apartment 11 of 2100 2nd Avenue, a well maintained building located off East 108th Street. Available for August 3rd occupancy, this renovated two bedroom, two bathroom apartment offers modern and comfortable living with features including an updated kitchen(with a dishwasher, wine fridge, and electric stove), a spacious living room, two queen sized bedrooms, and an in-unit washer and dryer. Both bedrooms fit queen beds and the first bedroom has an en-suite bathroom. Ideally located off East 108th Street, you will be 15 minutes from central park, walking distance to Mount Sinai, and steps to many of the neighborhood’s best restaurants and stores. You will also be a short walk to the 6 train and 3 blocks to the crosstown bus. The building has a virtual doorman. This is a walk up building, the apartment is on the second floor. Sorry no pets. Fee Breakdown: Fees to rent this apartment are 1st months rent, 1 month security deposit, 20 dollar application fee. Heat and hot water are included in the rent, tenant is responsible for electricity and internet. Tenants must make 40x the rent(155,000) and have good credit(680 and above). Guarantors(third party and personal) are welcome. Please text or call for showings or if you have questions. video- https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6q4xwJ4UN90&t=23s Sarah Rosenfeld(Real Estate Salesperson) (R New York) (646-335-8383)",
