        "description": "QR Code Link to This Post Best two bedroom deal in East Harlem. Welcome to apartment 9 of 212 East 105th Street, a well maintained building located in prime East Harlem. Available for August 1st occupancy, apartment 9 offers modern upgrades including a granite kitchen(with a dishwasher and wine cooler), a bright living room with east exposure, two queen sized bedrooms with courtyard views, a marble bathroom and an in-unit Bosch washer and dryer. Both bedrooms have closets and the apartment has an additional hall closet. An optimal apartment for those seeking comfort and modern living in one of Manhattan's most convenient neighborhood's. Ideally located between second and third avenue, you will be a short walk to Mount Sinai, Central Park and many of the neighborhood’s best restaurants and stores. This location is excellent for transportation as you will also be a 5 minute walk to the 6 train and two blocks to the crosstown bus. The building has a virtual doorman and a pet friendly policy. This is a walk up building, the apartment is on the third floor. Fee Breakdown: Fees to rent this apartment are 1st months rent, 1 month security deposit, 20 dollar application fee. Heat and hot water are included in the rent, tenant is responsible for electricity and internet. Tenants must have a combined income of 40x the monthly rent(139,000) and have good credit(680 and above). Guarantors(third party and personal) are welcome. Please call for showings or if you have questions. video- https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Acr_LvoRhig Sarah Rosenfeld(Real Estate Salesperson) (R New York) (646-335-8383)",
