        "description": "QR Code Link to This Post Looking for a 1 Bedroom for $1900-2000? YOU CAN HIRE A BROKER... We are showing 1BRs at a lower option of $1900 if hired as a tenant’s Broker vs. the \"no-fee\" option of $2200. PLEASE READ THE WHOLE LISTING & SEND YOUR INFO WE WILL NOT SHOW AN APT WITHOUT YOUR INFO Working with a Licensed Broker is legal and often the smarter choice. Many \"no‑fee\" listings simply build the fee into the rent, costing you more money over time. “No fee = higher rent” or “lower rent = with a fee,” and the lower‑rent option is usually cheaper overall. For example, $1900 (with a 1‑month broker fee) vs. $2200 (no fee) is a $3600 yearly difference. Rent increases are based on the lower‑rent amount. Please let us know in your email that you read this part and are aware of the broker fee. Classic 1BR ap in a walk-up building, perfect for a single occupant. Separate kitchen, ideal for cooking and dining at home. Spacious living room, bedroom, great closets, full bathroom. Walk UP. Steps from shops, restaurants, and cafes. Excellent transit access. Move-in ready by July 15. Unique apt, looking for the right person. Must be qualified. Please send your information + number: 👇No information, no response. Single/Couple— how many occupants Annual Income + Credit Score Earliest Move-in Date Pet info (type + size) Your Number: Guarantor info (if you need one) : Areas= This ad is for a 1BR in Kensington is $1900 with a 1 Month Broker fee BY CONTACTING US, YOUR AGREE TO WORK WORK WITH A LICENSED RE BROKER AND ACKNOWLEDGE THAT A BROKR'S FEE WILL APPLY ONLY IF YOU RENT ONE OF OUR UNITS. PLEASE... NO EMAILS ASKING \"IS THE APT AVAILABLE.\" WE WONT ANSWER. DONT WASTE OUR TIME. PLEASE SEND YOUR INFORMATION OR NO RESPONSE FROM US AT ALL GREAT/UNIQUE APT, LOOKING FOR GREAT PEOPLE! KENSINGTON| PROSPECT PARK SLOPE SOUTH GREENWOOD BROOKLYN",
