        "description": "QR Code Link to This Post Welcome to apartment 1E of 5 West 103rd Street, a modern and renovated three bedroom, two bathroom apartment located in the heart of Manhattan Valley. Available For September 1st occupancy, this residence features an upgraded kitchen (with dishwasher), a spacious living room with hardwood floors, three queen sized bedrooms, two full bathrooms and individual climate control. This apartment has a large private garden, a rare find in the neighborhood. There is a laundromat four blocks away. Ideally situated in a highly desirable location between Central Park West and Manhattan Avenue you will be across the street from Central Park and steps to many of the neighborhood’s best restaurants and stores. You will also be two blocks from the B and C train and one block from the M10 bus line providing seamless travel throughout Manhattan. There is no elevator in the building. The building is pet friendly and has a responsive management company. An ideal apartment for modern living in one of Manhattan's most convenient location's. Fee Breakdown: Fees to rent this apartment are 1st months rent, 1 month security deposit, 20 dollar application fee. Heat and hot water are included in the rent, tenants are responsible for electricity and internet. Tenants must have a combined income of 40x the monthly rent (227,000) and have good credit(680 and above). Guarantors(third party and personal) are welcome and must make 60x the monthly rent(341,000). Please call for showings or if you have questions. virtual tour- https://a.peek.us/viewer?token=Qj2nktJx Sarah Rosenfeld (Real Estate Salesperson) (R New York) (646-335-8383)",
